To terminate a C program, you can use the `exit()` function from the `stdlib.h` library. Here's an example of how to use it:

```c
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    // Your code here

    exit(EXIT_SUCCESS);
}
```

By calling `exit(EXIT_SUCCESS)`, the program will terminate successfully. This is a simple and effective way to end a C program.

